PEOPLE, Respondent, v. AH CHOY and JIM FOO, Appellants. No. 10,582; January 14, 1881. Criminal Law.—A Defendant has No Appeal from an order granting him a new trial. APPEAL from Superior Court, San Joaquin County.

McStay & Swinnerton and W. M. Gibson for appellants; A. L. Hart, attorney general, for respondent.

By the COURT.

The attorney general moves to dismiss the appeal taken by the defendant from an order of the superior court granting him a new trial. No such appeal is authorized by the Penal Code.

Appeal dismissed.
